* {{msg-mw|Exif-customrendered-1}}

exif-exposuremode:
{{exif-qqq}}

This tag shows if the photo's exposure was manually set or automatically determined. See the Wikipedia article on [[w:en:Exposure (photography)|exposure in photography]] for more details.

{{Related|Exif-exposuremode}}

exif-whitebalance:
{{exif-qqq}}

See also the Wikipedia article on [[w:Color balance|color balance]].

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Exif-whitebalance}}
* {{msg-mw|Exif-whitebalance-0}}
* {{msg-mw|Exif-whitebalance-1}}

exif-gaincontrol:
{{exif-qqq}}

Gain amplifies the signal off of the image sensor. Gain turns the brightness level up or down.

{{Related|Exif-gaincontrol}}

exif-gpslatituderef:
{{exif-qqq}}

In older versions of mediawiki this referred to if the latitude was North or South. This is no longer used in modern versions of mediawiki except for when using a foreign image repository that is using an older version of mediawiki since the information is now contained in {{msg-mw|exif-gpslatitude}}.

{{Related|Exif-gpslatitude}}

exif-gpslatitude:
{{exif-qqq}}

The latitude of the location from where the picture was taken from.

{{Related|Exif-gpslatitude}}
{{Identical|Latitude}}

exif-gpslongitude:
{{exif-qqq}}

The longitude of the location from where the picture was taken from.

{{Related|Exif-gpslatitude}}
{{Identical|Longitude}}

exif-gpsmeasuremode:
{{exif-qqq}}

This tag indicates whether the measurement 2D (latitude and longitude) or 3D (latitude, longitude, and altitude).

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Exif-gpsmeasuremode-2}}
* {{msg-mw|Exif-gpsmeasuremode-3}}

exif-gpsdop:
{{exif-qqq}}

How accurate the GPS information is. See [[wikipedia:Dilution of precision (GPS)]].

{{Related|Exif-gpsdop}}

exif-gpsdestlatitude:
{{exif-qqq}}

The latitude of the location shown in the picture, if it is different from latitude of the camera location. See {{msg-mw|exif-gpslatitude}}.

{{Related|Exif-gpslatitude}}
{{Identical|Latitude}}

exif-gpsdestlongitude:
{{exif-qqq}}

The longitude of the location shown in the picture, if it is different from longitude of the camera location. See {{msg-mw|exif-gpslongitude}}.

{{Related|Exif-gpslatitude}}
{{Identical|Longitude}}

exif-gpsdestdistanceref:
{{exif-qqq}}

Indicates the unit used to express the distance to the destination point. Values are typically "K", "M" or "N", standing for kilometers, miles and nautical miles, respectively. See also {{msg-mw|Exif-gpsspeedref}}.

{{Related|Exif-gpsdestdistance}}

exif-keywords:
{{exif-qqq}}

List of keywords for the photograph (or other media). This can come from IPTC-iim 2:25 keyword field, or XMP's dc:subject field.

{{Identical|Keyword}}

exif-headline:
{{exif-qqq}}

A short version of the image caption. The IPTC4XMP standard is clear that "this is not the same thing as title [ {{msg-mw|exif-objectname}} ]".

This is extracted from [http://www.iptc.org/std/photometadata/specification/IPTC-PhotoMetadata-201007_1.pdf XMP's photoshop:headline] and [http://www.iptc.org/std/IIM/4.1/specification/IIMV4.1.pdf IPTC-iim: 2:105 Headline tag].

{{Identical|Headline}}

exif-source:
{{exif-qqq}}

See [http://www.iptc.org/std/IIM/4.1/specification/IIMV4.1.pdf IPTC-iim standard 2:115].

This is who originally owned the image (a person, stock photo agency, etc). This does not refer to the image this image is based on.

{{Identical|Source}}

exif-urgency:
{{exif-qqq}}

Urgency. How urgent this image is. 1 is very urgent, 5 is normal, 8 is  very low priority.

{{Related|Exif-urgency}}

exif-objectcycle:
Time of day that media is intended for. Either morning only, evening only, or all day. Typically only used for news related things that might only be broadcast at a specific time of day.

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Exif-objectcycle-a}}
* {{msg-mw|Exif-objectcycle-p}}
* {{msg-mw|Exif-objectcycle-b}}

exif-languagecode:
{{exif-qqq}}

Language of image/media. This is taken from IPTC-iim 2:135 and XMP's dc:language.

{{Identical|Language}}

exif-iimcategory:
{{exif-qqq}}

Primary Category of image (or other media). Technically supposed to be limited to 3 characters, however that is not always followed. Some common 3 letter category abbreviations are expanded by mediawiki. Similar to {{msg-mw|exif-keywords}}.

{{Identical|Category}}

exif-datetimereleased:
{{exif-qqq}}

Earliest date the image (media) can be used.

See 2:30 of http://www.iptc.org/std/IIM/4.1/specification/IIMV4.1.pdf

exif-identifier:
{{exif-qqq}}
A formal identifier for the image. Often this is a URL.
{{Identical|Identifier}}

exif-label:
{{exif-qqq}}

Label given to the image for organizational purposes. This is very similar to {{msg-mw|exif-keywords}}. Label is more used by a person to organize their media, where keywords are used to describe the photo contents itself.

This property can come from xmp:Label in XMP ( http://www.adobe.com/content/dam/Adobe/en/devnet/xmp/pdfs/XMPSpecificationPart1.pdf ) or the label textual chunk in PNG.

{{Identical|Label}}

